 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Description<!--]--></p><div class="value text" data-v-da39b2d0><!--[--><p class="body" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Vrouwe Justitia staand voor twee terechtstellingen. Links op een bordes Zaleucus die zijn zoon een oog laat uitsteken. Rechts op een bordes Cambyses die een rechter laat villen. Op twee banderollen worden de straffen verklaard. Met tekst in het Frans en Nederlands in schoonschrift van Maria Strick.<!--]--></p><!--]--></div></li><li class="horizontal-stack-desktop object-data-properties-item" data-v-da39b2d0><p class="body name" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Inscriptions / marks<!--]--></p><div class="value text" data-v-da39b2d0><!--[--><p class="body" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->collector&#39;s mark: Lugt 2228<!--]--></p><!--]--></div></li><li class="horizontal-stack-desktop object-data-properties-item" data-v-da39b2d0><p class="body name" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Catalogue reference<!--]--></p><div class="value text" data-v-da39b2d0><!--[--><p class="body" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Hollstein Dutch 97<!--]--></p><!--]--></div></li><!--]--></ul></div><hr class="divider" data-v-6182f514 data-v-92cb05fc></div><div class="PropertyComponent object-data-component" data-v-6182f514><!----><div class="object-data-properties" data-v-6182f514 data-v-da39b2d0><h2 class="heading-4 object-data-properties-title" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Creation<!--]--></h2><ul class="object-data-properties-items" data-v-da39b2d0><!--[--><li class="horizontal-stack-desktop object-data-properties-item" data-v-da39b2d0><p class="body name" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->Creation<!--]--></p><div class="value text" data-v-da39b2d0><ul class="value-list" data-v-da39b2d0><!--[--><li class="body" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->printmaker: Willem Jacobsz Delff (mentioned on object), Delft<!--]--></li><li class="body" data-v-da39b2d0 data-v-5e6b56a7><!--[-->publisher: Robert